Testing #2218 

I would expect `Person` and `Person2` to behave the same given the JSDoc "types" `age` to be a `number`.

``` javascript
/**
 * @param {number} age
 */
function Person(age) {
    this.age = age; // <- it knows age is a number
}

function Person2() {
    this.age = 13;
}

var p1 = new Person();
var p2 = new Person2();

var a = p1.age; // <- it doesn't know this is a number
var b = p2.age; // <- it knows this is a number

```

Testing #2218 

For the following JS code I get no hover on `a1()`:

``` javascript
/**
 * This is a very cool function that is very nice.
 * @returns something
 */
function a1() {
        try {
                        throw new Error('x');         } catch(x) { x--; }
                        return 23;
}

x - a1()
```

If I remove the `@returns` from the js doc comment, then I get a hover, i.e. it works for this:

``` javascript
/**
 * This is a very cool function that is very nice.
 */
function a1() {
        try {
                        throw new Error('x');         } catch(x) { x--; }
                        return 23;
}

x - a1()

```

