Testing #2218 

``` javascript
function a1() {
    return 5;
}

function a2() {
    if (1) {
        return 5;
    } else {
        return '5';
    }
}
```

Hovering over a1() shows its return type is `number`. Hovering over a2() shows its return type is `any`. IMHO it should show `number|string` -- maybe this inference code was written before or types were introduced?

Testing #2218 

``` javascript
function xx() {
    if (true) {
        return 5;
    } else {
        return '5';
    }
}
```

This shows a squiggly on the second return saying 'Unreachable code detected'.

The following or any other const expression does not:

``` javascript
function xx() {
    if (true || true) {
        return 5;
    } else {
        return '5';
    }
}
```

same with `if (!false)` or `if (!true)`, etc.

